STEP 1: DEPLOY TO NETLIFY
--------------------------
1. Go to: https://app.netlify.com
2. Click "Add new site" → "Import an existing project"
3. Choose "Deploy with GitHub"
4. Authorize Netlify to access your GitHub
5. Select repository: "schedule-c-risk-scan"
6. Click "Deploy site"
7. Wait for deployment to complete (1-2 minutes)
8. You'll get a live URL like: https://random-name-123.netlify.app


STEP 2: SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
----------------------------------
1. In Netlify dashboard, go to: Site settings → Environment variables
2. Click "Add a variable" and add these 4 variables:

   Variable Name: AIRTABLE_TOKEN
   Value: [Paste your Airtable Personal Access Token]

   Variable Name: AIRTABLE_BASE_ID
   Value: [Paste your Base ID, starts with "app..."]

   Variable Name: AIRTABLE_CLIENTS_TABLE
   Value: Clients

   Variable Name: AIRTABLE_ASSESSMENTS_TABLE
   Value: Risk Assessments

3. Click "Save"
4. Go to: Deploys → Trigger deploy → Deploy site
   (This rebuilds with your environment variables)


STEP 3: GET AIRTABLE CREDENTIALS
---------------------------------
Personal Access Token:
1. Go to: https://airtable.com/create/tokens
2. Click "Create new token"
3. Name it: "Schedule C Risk Scan"
4. Add scopes: 
   - data.records:read
   - data.records:write
5. Add access to your base
6. Copy the token → Paste into AIRTABLE_TOKEN

Base ID:
1. Go to: https://airtable.com/api
2. Select your base
3. Copy the Base ID from the intro section → Paste into AIRTABLE_BASE_ID


STEP 4: SET UP AIRTABLE TABLES
-------------------------------
Create two tables in your Airtable base:

TABLE 1: "Clients"
Fields:
- First Name (Single line text)
- Last Name (Single line text)  
- Email (Email) ← Mark as primary field
- Business Name (Single line text)
- Business Type (Single select: Schedule C, LLC, S-Corp)
- Years in Business (Single select: 0-6 months, 6-12 months, 1-2 years, 2+ years)

TABLE 2: "Risk Assessments"
Fields:
- Client (Link to Clients table) ← IMPORTANT: Link to Clients
- First Name (Single line text)
- Last Name (Single line text)
- Email (Email)
- Business Name (Single line text)
- Business Type (Single line text)
- Years in Business (Single line text)
- Raw Score (Number)
- Max Possible Score (Number)
- Converted Score (Number)
- Stage (Single line text)
- Recommended Route (Long text)
- Risk Level (Single select: Low Risk, Moderate Risk, High Risk)
- Assessment Date (Date)


STEP 5: TEST YOUR DEPLOYMENT
-----------------------------
Test 1 - New Email:
1. Go to your Netlify URL
2. Complete the assessment with a NEW email (e.g., test1@example.com)
3. Submit the form
4. Check Airtable:
   ✓ New record should appear in "Clients" table
   ✓ New record should appear in "Risk Assessments" table
   ✓ Assessment should be LINKED to the client

Test 2 - Existing Email:
1. Complete another assessment using THE SAME email (test1@example.com)
2. Submit the form
3. Check Airtable:
   ✓ NO new client created (still only 1 client)
   ✓ NEW assessment created in "Risk Assessments"
   ✓ New assessment LINKED to existing client


TROUBLESHOOTING:
----------------
Problem: "Server configuration error"
Solution: Check that all 4 environment variables are set correctly in Netlify

Problem: "Failed to create client" or "Failed to create assessment"
Solution: 
- Verify table names match exactly: "Clients" and "Risk Assessments"
- Check that all fields exist in Airtable with correct names
- Ensure Airtable token has read AND write permissions

Problem: Function doesn't run
Solution: 
- Check Netlify Functions log: Site overview → Functions → View logs
- Verify netlify.toml is in root folder
- Redeploy: Deploys → Trigger deploy → Clear cache and deploy site

Problem: No data in Airtable
Solution:
- Open browser console (F12) and check for errors
- Verify the function URL works: https://your-site.netlify.app/.netlify/functions/submit
- Check Netlify Function logs for errors


